Types of Pensions
- Defined Benefit (DB)
  promise of a guaranteed future income one day like a salary
- Defined Contribution (DC)
  build up a pot of money
  
  - Personal Pension
    Stakeholder Pensions, SIPPs, Private Pensions
  - Workplace Pension
  
  
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 


Free Money 
Taxation
Growth
  - Defined Benefit (DB)
    pension accrual
    indexation
  - Defined Contribution (DC)
    pension fund
    grows by investment
 
 Money Out
   - Defined Benefit (DB)
    guaranteed future income like a salary
    lump sum commmutation
   - Defined Contribution (DC)
     25% tax-free cash
     annuity
     income drawdown    
 
 
 
